WEBVTT

00:02.587 --> 00:05.078
NARRA TOR:
Previously on Heroes.

00:06.007 --> 00:07.998
Camera's ready for whatever.

00:08.092 --> 00:09.298
What are you doing?

00:09.385 --> 00:10.966
(CLAIRE SCREAMING)

00:11.053 --> 00:12.179
Oh, my God.

00:12.263 --> 00:16.723
MOHINDER: When we embrace
what lies within,
our potential has no limit.

00:16.809 --> 00:19.471
And as far as you know,
that was attempt number one.

00:19.937 --> 00:22.019
MOHINDER: The future
is filled with promise,

00:22.106 --> 00:24.848
the present rife
with expectation.

00:25.985 --> 00:28.476
But when we deny
our instinct,

00:28.779 --> 00:31.191
and struggle against
our deepest urges...

00:31.282 --> 00:32.647
Are you on the list?

00:32.742 --> 00:34.198
...uncertainty begins.

00:34.285 --> 00:37.243
My dad obviously doesn't work
in a paper factory.

00:37.330 --> 00:38.866
I don't know what he does.

00:38.956 --> 00:40.207
(POLICE SIREN WAILING)

00:40.291 --> 00:41.246
COP: Go! Go! Go!

00:41.334 --> 00:42.699
Where is he?
Where's Sylar?

00:42.793 --> 00:44.624
l have no idea
what you're talking about.

00:44.712 --> 00:45.747
(GRUNTS)

00:45.838 --> 00:47.419
MOHINDER: Where does
this path lead?

00:47.506 --> 00:50.043
l have no idea
how you're pulling this off,
but I swear to God,

00:50.134 --> 00:52.125
I’m not going to stop
until / figure it out.
You understand me?

00:52.220 --> 00:54.256
MOHINDER:
When will the changes end?

00:54.764 --> 00:56.925
Is this transformation
a gift...
I just wanted to see my son.

00:57.058 --> 00:59.845
...ora curse?
You don't know anything
about power.

01:01.729 --> 01:04.186
And for those who fear
what lies ahead...

01:04.315 --> 01:07.022
PETER: / can’t control it.
NA THAN: Let me help you,
Peter.

01:07.109 --> 01:09.771
MOHINDER: ...the most important
question of all:

01:09.862 --> 01:12.103
Can we ever really change
what we are?

01:13.491 --> 01:14.822
(SCREAMING)

01:15.034 --> 01:16.274
(SCREAMING)

01:16.369 --> 01:17.654
(GASPING)

01:20.206 --> 01:22.413
PETER: Hey! Hey!

01:26.212 --> 01:28.294
What are you do...
Hey!

01:30.258 --> 01:31.498
You...

01:31.592 --> 01:33.503
You can see me.
You...

01:34.720 --> 01:36.221
Nobody can see me!

01:36.597 --> 01:38.804
I'm invisible.
MAN: What happened?

01:39.976 --> 01:41.762
MAN: ltjust sort of fell.
Who are you?

01:41.894 --> 01:45.933
How can you see me?
I, uh, I don't know.
ljust do what you can do.

01:47.525 --> 01:49.766
Fantastic. One of those.

01:50.194 --> 01:51.525
One of those?

01:51.988 --> 01:54.604
What do you mean?
You know someone
else like me?

01:54.699 --> 01:56.906
Hey, wait.
Where are you going?
You need to explain this.

01:56.993 --> 01:58.278
Look, I saw you.
What?

01:58.369 --> 01:59.984
I saw you in my dream.
Who are you?

02:00.079 --> 02:02.616
CLAUDE: Hey! I'm no one.
I'm the invisible man.

02:02.707 --> 02:05.414
I'm Claude Rains.
Now get away from me.
Forget you ever saw me.

02:05.501 --> 02:08.334
Yeah, but you know
what's happening to me.

02:09.213 --> 02:10.749
What is this? What...

02:11.007 --> 02:13.089
Listen, I found you.
I need you to help me.

02:13.175 --> 02:15.461
Why would I want to do that?
Because we're in danger.

02:15.553 --> 02:18.044
This entire city
is in danger.

02:18.222 --> 02:20.053
Yeah, it was in my dream.

02:22.310 --> 02:25.723
People die, we die.
I don't know when,
but it happens.

02:26.272 --> 02:27.478
Then you'd better
leave town.

02:27.565 --> 02:29.772
Hey! Where are you going?
You can't hide from me.

02:29.859 --> 02:32.976
I'm the invisible man.
I can walk around the corner
and disappear forever.

02:33.070 --> 02:35.447
Yeah, but I can see you.
I'm going to follow you.

02:35.531 --> 02:38.193
Smarter men than you
have tried
and they've paid for it.

02:38.284 --> 02:39.865
You stay away from me.

02:41.412 --> 02:43.073
And don't follow me!

02:48.377 --> 02:49.833
(WOMAN EXCLAIMS)

03:01.182 --> 03:02.388
(NlKl GASPS)

03:27.083 --> 03:29.449
Red elephant
with blue stripes?

03:30.669 --> 03:32.284
Pinstripe or plaid?

03:33.798 --> 03:36.540
Honey,lcant
see your thoughts.
I can only hear 'em.

03:38.469 --> 03:40.300
Oh, I have a good one.

03:41.430 --> 03:44.422
Wait, the ratty curtains
in our old apartment?

03:45.142 --> 03:46.302
(GROANS)

03:46.394 --> 03:48.134
How do you do that?

04:04.495 --> 04:06.531
DOCTOR: I'm not sure
what's happening.

04:06.622 --> 04:08.658
His vitals
are extremely irregular.

04:08.749 --> 04:11.240
After all we've done to him,
I'm not surprised.

04:11.335 --> 04:12.620
Keep him stabilized.

04:12.711 --> 04:14.622
There is another option.

04:19.385 --> 04:20.875
If he crashes,

04:21.846 --> 04:25.680
you bring him back again,
and again.

04:26.100 --> 04:27.260
(GASPS)

04:27.351 --> 04:30.343
When he dies,
it'll be on my terms,
not on his.

04:31.397 --> 04:32.682
Clear?

04:39.029 --> 04:40.985
ANDO: But I'm only
two minutes over.

04:41.073 --> 04:42.984
ATTENDANT: That'll be $48.50.

04:43.451 --> 04:44.782
For one-day parking?

04:44.869 --> 04:47.406
Hey, you want
your car back, or not?

05:05.723 --> 05:07.463
(SPEAKING IN JAPANESE)

05:12.730 --> 05:14.391
(SPEAKING IN JAPANESE)

05:22.198 --> 05:23.779
(SPEAKING IN JAPANESE)

06:00.778 --> 06:02.439
(CAR TIRES SCREECHING)

06:02.530 --> 06:04.942
Help!
There's a man
chasing us!

06:26.303 --> 06:27.713
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

06:34.603 --> 06:36.139
NATHAN: Dr. Suresh.

06:37.147 --> 06:38.728
Do you remember me?

06:38.816 --> 06:40.352
Nathan Petrelli.

06:40.651 --> 06:42.232
You yelled at my car.

06:42.319 --> 06:44.651
Yes, we met under
unfortunate circumstances.

06:44.738 --> 06:47.229
I believe I came off
as a deranged lunatic.

06:47.324 --> 06:48.825
Do you mind if I come in?

06:51.537 --> 06:53.653
I'm looking
for my brother, Doctor.

06:53.747 --> 06:55.328
That makes two of us.

06:55.416 --> 06:56.656
I'm sorry?

06:56.959 --> 06:59.917
I've been leaving messages
for him for two days now.

07:00.004 --> 07:01.619
I guess I'm in
the wrong place, then.

07:01.714 --> 07:04.421
I need to find him.
The last time I heard,
he was in Texas.

07:04.508 --> 07:05.918
He made it home, barely.

07:06.010 --> 07:08.046
Barely alive,
and now he's run off again.

07:08.137 --> 07:12.096
I'm afraid that he's gonna
somehow hurt people.

07:15.603 --> 07:18.766
Doctor, |, urn, lwas hoping
you could explain to me

07:19.440 --> 07:21.522
what the hell
is happening to him?

07:22.151 --> 07:24.893
Before his death,
my father compiled a list.

07:25.404 --> 07:29.693
Thirty-six individuals
who carry a genetic marker
which he discovered.

07:29.783 --> 07:34.026
A marker which he theorized
gave these people
certain abilities.

07:34.121 --> 07:36.863
And my brother
is one of them?
As are you.

07:41.295 --> 07:43.786
I didn't come here
to talk about me.
Fair enough.

07:43.881 --> 07:46.588
Peter's specific DNA
allows for a blend,

07:46.675 --> 07:48.176
like colors in a mosaic,

07:48.260 --> 07:50.967
resequencing itself
to mimic the abilities
of those around him.

07:51.055 --> 07:53.171
Like a chameleon.
More like a sponge.

07:53.265 --> 07:55.381
lt's precisely
why I've been
studying him.

07:55.476 --> 07:58.343
Could his condition
become dangerous to himself,
or to other people?

07:58.437 --> 08:01.804
If he absorbs too much
or comes into contact
with an unstable ability,

08:01.899 --> 08:03.810
then most definitely, yes.

08:04.568 --> 08:06.104
Can you fix it?

08:07.237 --> 08:09.319
Alter his genes somehow?

08:09.406 --> 08:12.648
Theoretically, it is
possible to develop
a specific site inhibitor,

08:12.743 --> 08:15.530
but, look, lwill know more
when we find him.
We?

08:17.581 --> 08:21.745
Doctor, the last thing
my brother needs is somebody
feeding into his paranoia.

08:22.336 --> 08:23.826
But thank you.

08:25.673 --> 08:27.083
Mr. Petrelli.

08:28.926 --> 08:30.382
Of all the people
on that list,

08:30.469 --> 08:32.926
your brother may be
the most important.

08:33.055 --> 08:35.171
If I can find him,
study him,

08:35.849 --> 08:38.101
then I can do
more than help him.

08:38.602 --> 08:40.467
Then I can help
all of you.

08:42.189 --> 08:44.931
Now, give me a minute,
and I'll get my coat.

08:51.657 --> 08:53.272
CLAUDE: lto|d you
not to follow me.

08:53.367 --> 08:55.028
PETER: I need help.

08:56.245 --> 08:57.701
You live up here?

08:58.706 --> 09:00.913
You're a fast learner,
aren't you, mate?

09:00.999 --> 09:03.081
I took care of a man
who owned this building.

09:03.168 --> 09:05.159
His name was
Charles Deveaux.

09:05.254 --> 09:06.790
Never heard of him.

09:07.297 --> 09:09.037
You don't think
that's strange?

09:09.133 --> 09:12.296
lworked here,
the place where you live
and keep your birds.

09:12.928 --> 09:14.384
CLAUDE: I don't keep anything.

09:14.471 --> 09:17.053
I let them out once a day.
They come back.

09:17.141 --> 09:19.132
Sounds like free will to me.

09:20.018 --> 09:23.055
I need to learn
how to control this,
like you do.

09:23.147 --> 09:25.103
What are you talking about?
It can't be controlled.

09:25.190 --> 09:28.557
Well, there has to be
some way. If I don't,
New York explodes.

09:28.652 --> 09:30.643
Okay? I explode.

09:32.072 --> 09:34.449
Exploding man.
Where did you
get that idea?

09:34.825 --> 09:37.282
My dreams. This place.

09:38.662 --> 09:40.493
I found you
for a reason.

09:40.581 --> 09:43.823
I think you're the one
that has to teach me
how to stop this.

09:44.668 --> 09:46.408
There's no such thing.

09:46.503 --> 09:48.960
No teaching,
no Sunday School
for the special.

09:49.047 --> 09:50.662
What I can do,
you can't learn.

09:50.758 --> 09:52.919
You wake up in the morning,
and it's there.

09:53.010 --> 09:55.592
If you've got thin soup,
then that's your supper.

09:55.679 --> 09:57.215
Sorry, mate.
That's the way it is.

09:57.306 --> 09:59.171
I'm trying not to die.

10:00.267 --> 10:01.598
There's got to be
something you can do.

10:01.685 --> 10:03.221
I can kill you myself,
right now,

10:03.312 --> 10:05.598
solve your
exploding problem here.

10:06.023 --> 10:07.888
Maybe that's why
you dreamt me.

10:08.859 --> 10:12.192
Don't bother looking for me.
You won't find me here again.

10:21.705 --> 10:24.993
So what exactly
am I looking for here?

10:25.083 --> 10:27.790
CLAIRE: Anything my dad
doesn't want us to find.

10:27.878 --> 10:30.119
You said you're good
with computers.

10:30.214 --> 10:32.296
I make movies
on my laptop.

10:33.383 --> 10:35.123
No, you're good
at finding those holes

10:35.219 --> 10:38.632
in that Internet
password-protected
nanny-blocker stuff.

10:38.722 --> 10:41.134
Shouldn't you be
watching the door?
What if your dad walks in?

10:41.225 --> 10:45.389
He's at work.
lt'sjust you, me,
and Mr. Muggles.

10:48.148 --> 10:49.479
There's nothing.

10:50.400 --> 10:52.356
(CHUCKLING)
There's not even any porn.
Gross.

10:52.444 --> 10:54.651
I'm serious.
This thing is totally clean.

10:54.738 --> 10:57.650
No. My dad lied to me
about my entire life,

10:57.741 --> 11:00.483
my biological parents,
my ability,

11:00.577 --> 11:02.488
you can't just
hide things like that.

11:02.579 --> 11:04.535
There's got to be
something on there.

11:04.623 --> 11:05.988
If your dad's the guy
you're describing,

11:06.083 --> 11:09.246
I don't think
he's gonna keep his secrets
on the family computer.

11:09.336 --> 11:10.917
(DOG BARKING)

11:12.923 --> 11:15.039
Uh-oh. Shut it down.
Go.

11:24.601 --> 11:26.137
Okay, okay.

11:26.770 --> 11:28.726
lthoughtyou
were at work.

11:31.191 --> 11:32.647
Forgot my cell.

11:33.026 --> 11:36.268
Zachary, what a nice surprise
to see you here.

11:37.406 --> 11:40.648
Yes, biology class.
We're lab partners now.

11:43.370 --> 11:46.203
Yeah, we were just doing
some research on the Internet.

11:46.290 --> 11:48.702
We have a presentation on...
The manatee,

11:49.251 --> 11:51.333
also known as the sea cow.

11:54.756 --> 11:58.294
Do you mind
if I talk to Claire
in private for a moment?

11:58.969 --> 12:00.800
CLAIRE: You can wait
in my room.

12:01.805 --> 12:04.171
lt's upstairs,
second door on the right.

12:08.061 --> 12:10.393
So, you and Zach?

12:10.480 --> 12:12.266
Miss Gomez
stuck us together.

12:12.357 --> 12:14.848
Must be some social
experiment or something.

12:15.235 --> 12:17.100
Worst day ever.

12:17.571 --> 12:18.777
Claire.

12:20.616 --> 12:21.651
What?

12:22.326 --> 12:25.568
You two used to be friends.
You might find you
actually get along.

12:35.172 --> 12:36.537
(SIGHING)

12:36.632 --> 12:37.997
Nice save.

12:38.967 --> 12:40.207
Thanks.

12:40.844 --> 12:42.175
So, what now?

12:44.514 --> 12:47.597
I need to talk to someone
who has some answers.

12:52.606 --> 12:54.722
What the hell
are you talking about?

12:57.861 --> 12:59.101
JANICE: Okay, wait.

12:59.947 --> 13:04.281
You're saying that
the guy with the glasses
actually abducted you?

13:05.577 --> 13:06.657
Yes.

13:07.746 --> 13:10.738
And he did this to you?
Yeah.

13:12.042 --> 13:14.328
Yeah, and I've got
to figure out how
he did this,

13:14.419 --> 13:18.537
and I'm gonna take him
and everybody with him down.
That Haitian guy, all of them.

13:21.009 --> 13:25.343
Matt, I'm sorry,
I've got to say,
this is all a little nuts.

13:26.056 --> 13:29.674
I mean, first
the whole psychic thing,
and now...

13:30.102 --> 13:31.763
God. Come on,
you're telling me

13:31.853 --> 13:33.980
you're about to run off
and chase some guy

13:34.106 --> 13:37.064
who works in a paper
factory in Texas?
They did this to me, Janice.

13:37.150 --> 13:38.686
I need to find them.

13:38.902 --> 13:41.393
l have to figure out
what this is all about.

13:42.239 --> 13:43.979
(THINKING)
Maybe you can call the FBI.

13:44.074 --> 13:47.362
No, I can't.
I can't go to the FBI.
They think I'm crazy.

13:49.871 --> 13:52.783
I've got to get ready.
I've got a review hearing
this morning.

13:52.874 --> 13:55.957
I'm about to get
my ass handed to me
by three captains.

14:07.973 --> 14:10.430
Yes, lwill call
the plumber today.

14:11.518 --> 14:13.884
Are you always
gonna be in my head?

14:14.146 --> 14:16.353
Well, I can't
control this thing.

14:16.815 --> 14:18.851
You can't,
or you won't?

14:22.112 --> 14:23.272
(HIRO SPEAKING JAPANESE)

14:23.363 --> 14:24.944
(AN DO SPEAKING JAPANESE)

14:56.730 --> 14:58.391
(CAR LOCK BEEPS)

14:58.482 --> 14:59.892
(CAR DOOR OPENS)

15:03.445 --> 15:04.981
(CAR ENGINE STARTING)

15:20.921 --> 15:22.582
(TIRES SCREECHING)

15:32.682 --> 15:35.765
ANDO: Oh! Oh! Hiro, Hiro!

15:37.354 --> 15:38.764
(EXCLAIMS)

15:38.855 --> 15:40.766
Who are you?
HlRO: Hey!

15:41.024 --> 15:42.184
Hello.

15:42.275 --> 15:43.651
Let me go.

15:44.778 --> 15:46.643
I am very special.

15:46.738 --> 15:48.524
I offer myself in trade.

15:49.658 --> 15:54.118
Release unspecial Ando,
and | go with you. Okay?

15:56.456 --> 15:57.662
(GRUNTING)

15:57.749 --> 16:00.035
Good deal, yes?

16:00.335 --> 16:02.417
What are you doing?

16:02.712 --> 16:04.543
You no like the good deal?

16:08.343 --> 16:10.049
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

16:28.280 --> 16:30.271
Why did you take
that off me?

16:30.365 --> 16:33.072
I'm Dr. Witherson.
I'm a psychiatrist.

16:33.493 --> 16:35.154
And I have been assigned
to your case.

16:35.245 --> 16:37.782
Go. You shouldn't be in here.
It's not safe.

16:37.914 --> 16:39.199
If it makes you feel
more comfortable,

16:39.291 --> 16:41.156
we can put the restraints
back on while we talk.

16:41.251 --> 16:44.243
You don't understand.
The drugs keep her weak.

16:44.796 --> 16:47.333
That jacket can't stop her.
Give me a shot.

16:47.424 --> 16:48.960
You mean Jessica?

16:49.050 --> 16:50.836
How do you know her name?

16:50.927 --> 16:52.508
| read your file.

16:52.596 --> 16:56.589
I know all about your past,
your marriage, your website,
your sister.

16:56.850 --> 16:58.181
Her accident.

16:59.186 --> 17:01.723
Her name was Jessica, too,
isn't that right?

17:03.356 --> 17:04.892
Give me another shot.

17:04.983 --> 17:08.146
You know, I haven't made
an official diagnosis yet,

17:08.236 --> 17:10.477
but it seems like
we're dealing with

17:10.572 --> 17:13.780
a classic case of
multiple personality disorder.

17:14.242 --> 17:16.278
You're wasting your time.

17:18.413 --> 17:19.698
Just go.

17:19.789 --> 17:22.041
You know...
It's okay, it's okay.

17:25.962 --> 17:28.294
It makes sense,
facing the kind of sentence

17:28.381 --> 17:30.372
that you're facing,
that you want to give up.

17:30.467 --> 17:33.129
You think your life is over,
but it's not.

17:33.220 --> 17:36.212
You can still make something
of yourself in here.

17:36.306 --> 17:40.015
People do it all the time,
but you've got to want help.

17:40.560 --> 17:41.936
And, yeah,

17:42.020 --> 17:44.727
it can take years to integrate
a multiple personality,

17:44.814 --> 17:46.520
but if you let me,

17:48.151 --> 17:49.482
I can help you.

17:49.986 --> 17:52.272
What I am, you can't fix.

17:53.490 --> 17:56.072
Just give me another shot,
and go away.

17:56.159 --> 17:57.194
No.

18:12.842 --> 18:16.460
Oh, man,
I'm trying to pay this rent.

18:17.973 --> 18:20.430
You know,
it would really help if you...

18:22.394 --> 18:24.134
No, it's cool. It's cool.

18:24.521 --> 18:26.682
I know you would if you could.

18:27.899 --> 18:29.355
Thanks, anyway.

18:33.029 --> 18:35.611
So, have you seen
my lunch box or not?

18:35.699 --> 18:38.406
I don't know.
It's wherever you left it.

18:38.785 --> 18:41.026
I left it in the car.
Then that's where it is.

18:41.121 --> 18:42.861
Okay, so where's the car?

18:43.665 --> 18:45.656
The car's in the shop. Micah?

18:45.792 --> 18:49.034
So you lost my lunch box?
I didn't lose anything.
It's in the car.

18:49.129 --> 18:51.871
Fine. You make
bad lunch anyways.

18:53.842 --> 18:56.675
Micah! Micah!

18:58.763 --> 19:01.470
It's not my fault
you can't keep track
of your own stuff.

19:01.558 --> 19:04.470
Morn always put my lunch
in my backpack
every single morning.

19:04.561 --> 19:05.676
Well, I'm not your mom.

19:05.770 --> 19:06.885
Yeah, that's for sure.

19:06.980 --> 19:09.562
Micah, this isn't easy.

19:09.816 --> 19:11.898
It wasn't easy
for Mom, either.

19:11.985 --> 19:15.022
But she always found a way
of making some money, Dad.

19:15.739 --> 19:17.275
I'm late for school.

19:32.547 --> 19:35.380
Do you have any idea
how dangerous this is?

19:35.467 --> 19:39.051
You said if I had an emergency
to hang the chimes
outside my window.

19:39.137 --> 19:41.173
Is your father
becoming suspicious?

19:41.264 --> 19:44.677
No, and it's
kind of a problem.

19:45.810 --> 19:48.597
Every word out of my mouth
is a lie.

19:48.897 --> 19:52.731
l have to laugh and smile
and look him in the eye.

19:52.817 --> 19:54.523
My own father.

19:54.611 --> 19:56.442
lt's breaking my heart.

19:56.529 --> 19:58.781
Would you prefer
I took your memory?

19:59.741 --> 20:04.451
I need to know that one thing
in my life is real.

20:08.124 --> 20:10.536
Do you know
who my real parents are?

20:19.469 --> 20:21.801
Of your father,
I know nothing.

20:23.556 --> 20:25.092
And my mother?

20:28.144 --> 20:30.305
Only that she died
in an explosion

20:30.397 --> 20:32.683
here in Texas,
14 years ago.

20:33.983 --> 20:35.564
My mother died?

20:38.571 --> 20:40.072
Are you sure?

20:40.156 --> 20:41.771
Your father told me
many years ago.

20:41.866 --> 20:43.606
He had no reason to lie.

20:48.957 --> 20:52.324
This is the last conversation
we have about this.

20:52.710 --> 20:54.701
Now you need
to go back home,

20:55.171 --> 20:58.004
and forget
about your real parents.

21:15.859 --> 21:18.441
The groomer missed
one of Mr. Muggles' nails.

21:18.528 --> 21:20.940
I'm gonna run him back
by the shop before they close.

21:21.030 --> 21:23.237
Don't want you scratching
up my wood floors.

21:23.324 --> 21:24.825
No, we don't.

21:25.118 --> 21:26.449
Where's Claire?

21:26.536 --> 21:29.994
She's at the library
getting books
for some biology report.

21:30.081 --> 21:32.948
I cannot believe
how many projects
they lay on these kids.

21:33.042 --> 21:35.454
I don't know
how she holds everything
in that head of hers.

21:35.545 --> 21:36.955
No, I don't.

21:39.299 --> 21:41.460
You're still worried
about her, aren't you?

21:41.551 --> 21:42.791
She's had a rough
couple of weeks.

21:42.886 --> 21:45.468
Well, besides
a little memory loss,

21:45.555 --> 21:48.297
I'd say she's doing
just peachy.

21:48.892 --> 21:50.257
Do you really?

21:50.643 --> 21:53.225
lt's Lyle
you need to worry about.

21:53.730 --> 21:57.143
That boy is getting
so absent-minded lately.

21:57.233 --> 21:59.019
Yes, yes, we'll be back.

22:00.236 --> 22:01.897
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

22:06.326 --> 22:08.567
Yes?
I did everything I could.

22:09.454 --> 22:10.739
He's dead.

22:12.499 --> 22:14.581
Well, that's less than ideal.

22:15.418 --> 22:17.579
What do you want me
to do with the body?

22:19.088 --> 22:20.794
Get it ready for shipping.

22:21.216 --> 22:22.831
I'll be in later.

22:48.701 --> 22:53.365
ZACH: There was a fire
in an apartment house
14 years ago in Kermit, Texas.

22:53.456 --> 22:56.072
Kermit, why does that
sound so familiar?

22:56.793 --> 22:58.283
Because of the frog?

23:00.088 --> 23:01.544
Check it out.

23:01.631 --> 23:05.590
A 21-year-old woman
was killed in the explosion,
Meredith Gordon.

23:05.760 --> 23:07.000
CLAIRE: Oh, my God.

23:07.095 --> 23:10.178
Also killed in the fire
was her 18-month-old daughter.

23:11.558 --> 23:13.298
Claire, I think that's you.

23:14.477 --> 23:16.013
But I didn't die.

23:16.646 --> 23:18.637
Somebody thought you did.

23:19.482 --> 23:21.347
What am I supposed to do
with all of this?

23:21.442 --> 23:22.898
You may still have
a real family out there.

23:22.986 --> 23:26.023
Maybe you've got an aunt,
or a rich eccentric uncle.

23:27.323 --> 23:28.779
Great, an uncle.

23:31.327 --> 23:35.070
Who knows?
One of them might even know
who your real father is.

23:45.008 --> 23:46.248
Well,

23:47.844 --> 23:50.005
I'm surprised you left out
the flying saucers.

23:50.096 --> 23:52.132
Officer Parkman,
is this really
the statement

23:52.223 --> 23:54.930
you want entered
into your public record?

23:55.143 --> 23:57.384
That a paper salesman
from Odessa, Texas,

23:57.478 --> 24:01.312
is currently harboring
a super-powered serial killer,

24:01.691 --> 24:03.682
and that you raided
his warehouse on a hunch?

24:04.694 --> 24:08.186
Sir, all I've ever
wanted to do was
protect and serve,

24:09.198 --> 24:12.031
to help my fellow man.
I'll ask you again.

24:12.118 --> 24:15.155
Do you want your future
as a police officer

24:15.246 --> 24:18.079
to be decided by
what you've written here?

24:18.833 --> 24:22.325
Just say yes, so I can
flush it down the toilet.

24:25.340 --> 24:28.582
At this time,
I'd like to recant
my previous written statement.

24:28.676 --> 24:30.712
I made the whole thing up.

24:32.055 --> 24:33.261
Why did you do that?

24:33.348 --> 24:36.215
I failed to make detective
three times, sir, and, uh,

24:37.268 --> 24:41.352
quite frankly, I was siCk
of directing traffic,
handing out speeding tickets,

24:41.606 --> 24:43.688
and I wanted to look
like a hero.

24:44.734 --> 24:48.477
I am sorry for any shame
that I may have brought
this department.

24:49.447 --> 24:52.735
Great, a liar, not a nutcase.

24:55.244 --> 24:59.954
Officer Parkman,
pending review of your case
by a Civilian ombudsman

25:00.416 --> 25:01.792
and union representative,

25:01.876 --> 25:05.664
we're enforCing
a six-month suspension
of your active duties.

25:06.839 --> 25:09.330
We're gonna need your gun
and your badge.

25:23.648 --> 25:24.854
Janice?

25:24.941 --> 25:27.182
JANICE: Matt,
will you come upstairs?

25:28.444 --> 25:29.820
(WATER FLOWlNG)

25:30.405 --> 25:31.690
Oh, Matt!

25:32.115 --> 25:33.400
What?

25:33.700 --> 25:35.406
Now are you gonna
fix the pipes?

25:35.493 --> 25:37.449
Oh, God.
Give me a wrenCh.

25:41.040 --> 25:42.200
(GRUNTING)

25:43.793 --> 25:45.784
HlRO: Where are you taking us?

25:47.380 --> 25:49.166
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

25:54.387 --> 25:57.629
Tell your boss
I'm on very
important mission.

25:58.641 --> 26:03.101
I know all about
your so-called mission to
save the world, Mr. Nakamura.

26:03.479 --> 26:07.518
You think you have a power,
and that you can use it
to make a difference.

26:09.110 --> 26:10.816
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

26:33.801 --> 26:35.632
Two first-Class tickets,

26:35.887 --> 26:38.253
non-stop to Tokyo.
First-Class?

27:29.565 --> 27:31.305
You aren't answering
your cell phone.

27:31.400 --> 27:33.527
I've been looking
everywhere for you.

27:33.611 --> 27:34.646
What's he doing here?

27:34.779 --> 27:36.315
Making up
for past mistakes.

27:36.405 --> 27:37.941
I'd like to help you.

27:40.660 --> 27:41.740
You leaving town?

27:41.828 --> 27:45.320
Yeah, I think I'd get away
for a little while.

27:46.040 --> 27:48.497
What? Be a danger
to somebody else?

27:48.584 --> 27:50.791
There's got to be
another way, Peter.
Let me help you.

27:50.878 --> 27:52.414
You can't.
But maybe I can.

27:52.463 --> 27:54.169
How?
We find that
answer together.

27:54.257 --> 27:57.249
If you allow me to test you
with more research, I...

27:58.010 --> 28:01.218
So you can cure me?
You're gonna fix all of this.

28:01.305 --> 28:03.170
It will take study
and then time.

28:03.266 --> 28:05.928
Time? I don't have time
to be your guinea pig.

28:06.060 --> 28:08.472
l have a plane to catch.
I'm not letting you
run away, Peter.

28:08.563 --> 28:11.521
So, what,
you're gonna call
the cops on me, Nathan?

28:11.607 --> 28:13.689
You gonna tell them
your brother's going nuclear?

28:13.776 --> 28:16.518
I could have my mentally
ill brother detained.

28:17.196 --> 28:18.902
For his own safety.

28:30.293 --> 28:32.284
I know you want
to help me.

28:33.045 --> 28:36.537
You're my big brother,
you fix everything,
but you can't...

28:37.008 --> 28:38.794
You can't fix this one
this time.

28:38.885 --> 28:41.376
I can.
Look, let's just sit down.

28:41.470 --> 28:43.131
We can figure this out.

28:45.725 --> 28:46.965
Okay.
Okay?

28:48.019 --> 28:49.304
Okay.

28:52.315 --> 28:53.600
Peter!

28:56.193 --> 28:57.729
Where did he go?
GUARD: Who?

28:57.820 --> 28:59.526
You're supposed
to watch the door.

28:59.614 --> 29:00.979
My God, did hejust...

29:01.073 --> 29:03.280
Get down to the airport,
and make sure he doesn't
get away this time.

29:03.367 --> 29:04.482
Yes, sir.

29:24.388 --> 29:27.221
PETER: Yeah,
just help yourself.
CLAUDE: Your place?

29:27.308 --> 29:28.297
Yeah.

29:28.392 --> 29:31.259
Guy with family connections
like yours could do
a lot better.

29:31.354 --> 29:33.720
Left the family business.
I'm a nurse now.

29:33.814 --> 29:35.975
Nurse who's an empath,
very cute.

29:36.108 --> 29:37.484
Empath, what's that mean?

29:37.568 --> 29:40.025
It means you're a pain
in my ass, mate.

29:40.655 --> 29:42.691
Yeah, but you're following me.

29:43.199 --> 29:45.030
Yeah, well,
I'm not very much
of a people person,

29:45.117 --> 29:47.199
but I'm certainly not gonna
let you kill them all.

29:47.703 --> 29:50.194
You seemed pretty sure
about that pending
apocalypse of yours.

29:50.289 --> 29:52.996
Yeah, not unless
you help me control it.

29:53.125 --> 29:55.332
You don't know
what you're asking,
what you have to go through.

29:55.419 --> 29:57.284
You might want
to reconsider dying.

29:57.380 --> 29:59.587
Hell of a lot easier.
I can handle it.

29:59.674 --> 30:01.881
Yeah, that's what
they all say.

30:02.551 --> 30:03.631
They?

30:04.512 --> 30:07.219
(STAMMERING) How many people
have you taught before me?

30:10.893 --> 30:13.350
Come on, mate,
l'll steal us a cab.

30:16.774 --> 30:18.435
You coming or not?

30:26.325 --> 30:27.656
(GRUNTING)

30:28.911 --> 30:30.117
(SIGHS)

30:43.050 --> 30:45.541
So they suspended me
for six months.

30:47.763 --> 30:48.923
Oh, Matt.

30:50.016 --> 30:52.849
I actually thought
this ability was gonna
be a good thing,

30:52.935 --> 30:56.803
and now I'm unemployed
and about to lose
my marriage.

31:01.110 --> 31:02.941
You haven't lost that.

31:03.487 --> 31:04.988
Not yet, anyway.

31:05.072 --> 31:07.154
Thanks, that's encouraging.

31:08.701 --> 31:10.066
Look, we...

31:12.038 --> 31:14.370
We just have to
trust each other.

31:16.459 --> 31:17.949
I can do that.

31:25.342 --> 31:26.468
Yeah.

31:29.680 --> 31:32.422
So I'm gonna give you
one more freebie.

31:34.435 --> 31:36.141
What am I thinking?

31:41.317 --> 31:43.103
We're having a baby?

31:46.739 --> 31:47.899
(SlGHlNG)

31:47.990 --> 31:49.981
We're having a baby!

31:50.076 --> 31:51.612
(BOTH LAUGHING)

31:59.210 --> 32:01.542
Nik, what have
they done to you?

32:03.589 --> 32:05.875
If they catch you...
They won't.

32:08.135 --> 32:10.797
Come Closer.
What is it?

32:12.681 --> 32:14.057
Your shirt.

32:15.684 --> 32:17.424
It smells like home.

32:19.563 --> 32:21.019
How's Micah?

32:23.609 --> 32:25.395
Is he okay?
He's fine.

32:27.822 --> 32:29.187
It's just...

32:31.158 --> 32:33.991
I can't do this, Nik.
Not alone.

32:35.955 --> 32:38.162
I thought I could.
I thought I could handle
everything, but...

32:38.249 --> 32:40.456
D.L., you can't
do this to me.

32:40.668 --> 32:43.410
l have got to find a way
to get you out of here.

32:44.338 --> 32:45.453
This is crazy.

32:45.548 --> 32:47.084
I can walk in here
any time I want, right?

32:47.174 --> 32:48.584
I should be able
to get you out.

32:48.676 --> 32:52.840
lam going to be
in here for a long time.
The rest of my life, maybe.

32:54.515 --> 32:57.632
You need to get used to that.
Your son needs you.

32:57.726 --> 33:00.058
Damn it, D.L.,
that is not fair.

33:01.063 --> 33:03.179
lam counting on you.

33:04.567 --> 33:06.853
And you know
that I need to stay in here.

33:06.944 --> 33:08.559
I need you, Nik.

33:10.573 --> 33:11.938
We need you.

33:14.076 --> 33:16.783
He's having such a hard time
without you.

33:17.663 --> 33:19.619
You need to talk to him.

33:21.458 --> 33:23.323
You need to be honest.

33:24.503 --> 33:27.415
He needs boundaries,
and a strong hand.

33:31.552 --> 33:33.167
It's not too late.

33:39.602 --> 33:41.138
You need to go.

33:43.439 --> 33:44.428
Go.

34:06.545 --> 34:08.285
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

34:41.247 --> 34:45.331
CLAIRE: There's only
12 people in Kermit
with the last name Gordon.

34:46.502 --> 34:48.242
So far, only three.

34:48.963 --> 34:51.500
None of them
have ever heard of Meredith.

34:51.590 --> 34:53.126
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

34:53.342 --> 34:55.082
MR. BENNET: Claire?

34:56.095 --> 34:57.801
I'll call you back.

34:57.888 --> 34:59.094
Claire.

35:00.224 --> 35:01.839
Sorry, I was just

35:02.893 --> 35:04.929
talking to Zach
about our report.

35:05.020 --> 35:06.430
Ah, well.

35:06.730 --> 35:10.222
Molly in accounting
is married to
a marine biologist,

35:10.317 --> 35:12.182
and he said that...

35:12.987 --> 35:15.103
You're already
on top of it.

35:16.532 --> 35:18.523
Did you know that
all three varieties
of the manatee

35:18.617 --> 35:20.448
are vulnerable
to extinction?

35:20.536 --> 35:22.026
No, I didn't.

35:29.044 --> 35:31.000
Is everything
all right?

35:31.171 --> 35:33.378
We haven't talked
in a while.

35:34.383 --> 35:36.590
Actually,
there is something.

35:37.094 --> 35:38.209
Yeah?

35:41.348 --> 35:44.090
The bears,
my stuffed bears.

35:45.644 --> 35:48.260
I think it's time
for them to migrate.

35:50.774 --> 35:53.732
I'm almost 16, Dad.
Bears and talks
can't last forever.

35:54.361 --> 35:58.149
Whether you're 16,
or32,or64u.

35:58.407 --> 36:01.740
When I'm 64, you'll be...
...I will be there for you.

36:03.620 --> 36:04.826
Always.

36:08.792 --> 36:11.750
Don't you think it's time
I learn how to deal
with my own problems?

36:24.224 --> 36:27.682
Well, dinner's in an hour,
and just do me a favor.

36:27.770 --> 36:30.682
No extinction talk
at the table.

36:31.857 --> 36:34.439
You know how sensitive
your mother is.

36:49.792 --> 36:51.282
(DOOR BUZZING)

36:53.921 --> 36:56.879
You had a Change of heart?
My son.

37:01.553 --> 37:03.839
My family
needs me, so...

37:04.640 --> 37:07.382
I want you to understand
that there are no guarantees.

37:07.476 --> 37:10.843
I don't care.
I need to get
rid of Jessica.

37:12.773 --> 37:14.980
So, you know what might help?

37:17.778 --> 37:19.643
If I could talk to her.

37:20.989 --> 37:21.978
All right?

37:22.074 --> 37:24.190
Isn't there another way?
No.

37:24.785 --> 37:26.321
I'm afraid
in cases like these,

37:26.412 --> 37:28.403
it is imperative
that l have interaction

37:28.497 --> 37:31.489
with all aspects
of the patient's personality.

37:31.834 --> 37:34.246
Honey, let me talk to her.

37:34.336 --> 37:35.371
No.

37:36.922 --> 37:38.253
You can't.

37:39.675 --> 37:41.040
So, let me put it to you
this way.

37:41.135 --> 37:42.420
EHherlspeak
with Jessica,

37:42.511 --> 37:46.299
or you may not see
your little boy
for a very, very long time.

38:00.362 --> 38:01.397
Bye.

38:02.448 --> 38:03.528
Wait.

38:14.084 --> 38:17.167
Micah, where have you been?
I was worried to death.

38:17.254 --> 38:19.461
l was just out
walking around.

38:20.299 --> 38:21.539
Sit down.

38:29.600 --> 38:32.091
Micah, we've got to
figure this out,

38:32.478 --> 38:35.060
because the truth is
your mom's not coming home.

38:35.147 --> 38:37.638
I'm having
a really hard time, here.

38:38.233 --> 38:39.894
I can't get a job.

38:40.819 --> 38:42.810
I can barely pay the rent.

38:42.905 --> 38:47.148
I never felt much
like a man in my life.

38:49.161 --> 38:51.197
My father never taught me,

38:51.914 --> 38:54.371
but I want to be
a good dad to you.

38:55.334 --> 38:57.575
But I'm gonna
need your help.

38:57.878 --> 39:00.164
We've got to pull together,
and make this work,

39:00.255 --> 39:02.120
because it's just
you and me.

39:02.216 --> 39:05.083
I'm sorry, Dad.
I can try harder.

39:12.643 --> 39:14.429
Maybe this will help.

39:23.195 --> 39:26.278
Where'd you get...
Where'd you get this from?

39:27.407 --> 39:30.069
You know how you and mom
have a secret?

39:31.828 --> 39:33.955
Well, I have a secret, too.

39:52.140 --> 39:53.596
(SPEAKING IN JAPANESE)

39:58.480 --> 40:00.311
That's up to the Boss.

40:08.740 --> 40:10.196
(SPEAKING IN JAPANESE)

40:15.330 --> 40:16.831
(SPEAKING IN JAPANESE)

40:55.954 --> 40:57.194
(SlGHlNG)

40:58.707 --> 41:00.197
WOMAN: Hello?

41:00.917 --> 41:04.159
Hi, I'm looking for someone
related to Meredith Gordon.

41:04.254 --> 41:06.370
She died in an explosion
14 years ago.

41:06.465 --> 41:08.956
I’ve been calling
everyone in Kermit

41:09.176 --> 41:11.212
with the last name
of Gordon.

41:11.303 --> 41:13.885
Any chance
that you’re related to her?

41:13.972 --> 41:15.303
Who is this?

41:15.390 --> 41:18.553
My name's Claire Bennet.
I'm calling from Odessa.

41:18.644 --> 41:21.056
(STAMMERING)
What is this about?

41:21.146 --> 41:23.307
And how do you know
the name Meredith Gordon?

41:24.232 --> 41:26.143
I think she was my mom.

41:26.943 --> 41:28.558
Is this some kind ofjoke?

41:29.363 --> 41:30.694
No, ma'am.

41:32.616 --> 41:35.073
Well, Meredith
only had one daughter,

41:35.160 --> 41:37.321
and she died in the fire.

41:39.373 --> 41:43.082
Well, that's kind of
what I'm trying to say,
is I didn't die.

41:44.086 --> 41:45.121
I think I'm her,

41:45.212 --> 41:48.204
and I'm looking
for any information
I can find about my mom.

41:50.592 --> 41:53.004
Well, then you made
the right call.

41:53.595 --> 41:54.960
This is her.

41:56.390 --> 41:57.425
Mom?

42:07.275 --> 42:08.355
Yeah.

42:30.298 --> 42:31.799
(DOOR CLOSING)

42:42.644 --> 42:44.145
How's Claire?
